bio: I'm Naval, a serial entrepreneur, investor, and writer. I'm the founder of AngelList, AngelList Syndicates, AngelList Talent, and AngelList Venture. I'm also an investor in over 100 startups, including Twitter, Uber, and Coinbase. I'm the author of the best-selling book, 'The Ultimate Startup Guide', and I write a daily newsletter called 'AngelList Daily'.

Elon Musk is an entrepreneur and business magnate. He is the founder, CEO, CTO and chief designer of SpaceX; early stage investor, CEO and product architect of Tesla, Inc.; founder of The Boring Company; co-founder of Neuralink; and co-founder and initial co-chairman of OpenAI. A centibillionaire, Musk is one of the richest people in the world.

Marc Andreessen is an American entrepreneur, venture capitalist, and software engineer. He is best known as the co-founder of Netscape Communications Corporation, the co-founder of Andreessen Horowitz, and the co-author of Mosaic, the first widely used web browser.

Jeff Bezos is an American technology and retail entrepreneur, investor, and philanthropist. He is best known as the founder, chairman, and chief executive officer of Amazon.com. He is currently the richest person in the world, with a net worth of $177.5 billion as of February 2021.

William Henry Gates III is an American business magnate, software developer, investor, author, and philanthropist. He is best known as the co-founder of Microsoft Corporation. During his career at Microsoft, Gates held the positions of chairman, CEO and chief software architect, and remains the largest individual shareholder with 1.75% of the common stock.

Mark Elliot Zuckerberg is an American technology entrepreneur and philanthropist. He is known for co-founding and leading Facebook as its chairman and chief executive officer. He also is a co-founder of the solar sail spacecraft development project Breakthrough Starshot and the nonprofit organization Fwd: Thinking.

Steven Paul Jobs was an American business magnate, industrial designer, investor, and media proprietor. He was the chairman, chief executive officer (CEO), and co-founder of Apple Inc.; CEO and majority shareholder of Pixar; a member of The Walt Disney Company's board of directors following its acquisition of Pixar; and founder, chairman, and CEO of

Warren Edward Buffett is an American business magnate, investor, and philanthropist. He is considered by some to be one of the most successful investors in the world and has a net worth of $84.6 billion as of February 2021. He is the chairman and CEO of Berkshire Hathaway, and is consistently ranked among the world's wealthiest people.

Balaji Srinivasan is an American entrepreneur, investor, and writer. He is the founder of 21.co, a decentralized finance company, and CoinList, a platform for token sales. He is also a partner at Andreessen Horowitz, a venture capital firm, and a co-founder of the Bitcoin Foundation.
Akira The Don is a rapper, producer, and entrepreneur. He is the founder of the record label Akira The Don Records and the clothing brand Akira The Don.

Samuel Altman is an American entrepreneur and investor. He is the president of Y Combinator, a startup accelerator, and the founder of OpenAI, a nonprofit research company. He is also the co-founder of the venture capital firm Initialized Capital.
